definition.value: a sore throat AE that has Severe pain; limiting self care ADL; limiting ability to swallow
a stridor AE that has respiratory distress limiting self care ADL; medical intervention indicated
a stridor AE that has life-threatening airway compromise; urgent intervention indicated (e.g., tracheotomy or intubation)
a voice alteration AE that has mild or intermittent change from normal voice
a voice alteration AE that has moderate or persistent change from normal voice; still understandable

a voice alteration AE that has severe voice changes including predominantly whispered speech; may require frequent repetition or face-to-face contact for understandability; may require assistive technology
a wheezing AE that has detectable airway noise with minimal symptoms
a wheezing AE that has severe respiratory symptoms limiting self care ADL; oxygen therapy or hospitalization indicated
a menorrhagia AE that has moderate symptoms; medical intervention indicated (e.g., hormones)
a menorrhagia AE that has severe; transfusion indicated; surgical intervention indicated (e.g., hysterectomy)
an acute kidney injury AE that has creatinine level increase of >0.3 mg/dL; creatinine 1.5 - 2.0 x above baseline
an acute kidney injury AE that has creatinine 2 - 3 x above baseline
an acute kidney injury AE that has creatinine >3 x baseline or >4.0 mg/dL; hospitalization indicated
a hematuria AE that has symptomatic; urinary catheter or bladder irrigation indicated; limiting instrumental ADL
a hematuria AE that has gross hematuria; transfusion, IV medications or hospitalization indicated; elective endoscopic, radiologic or operative intervention indicated; limiting self care ADL
an urinary incontinence AE that has occasional (e.g., with coughing, sneezing, etc.), pads not indicated
an urinary incontinence AE that has spontaneous; pads indicated; limiting instrumental ADL
an urinary incontinence AE that has Intervention indicated (e.g., clamp, collagen injections); operative intervention indicated; limiting self care ADL
an urinary retention AE that has urinary, suprapubic or intermittent catheter placement not indicated; able to void with some residual
an urinary retention AE that has placement of urinary, suprapubic or intermittent catheter placement indicated; medication indicated
an urinary retention AE that has elective operative or radiologic intervention indicated; substantial loss of affected kidney function or mass
a suicidal ideation AE that has increased thoughts of death but no wish to kill oneself
a suicidal ideation AE that has suicidal ideation with no specific plan or intent
a suicidal ideation AE that has specific plan to commit suicide without serious intent to die which may not require hospitalization
a suicidal ideation AE that has specific plan to commit suicide with serious intent to die which requires hospitalization
a suicide attempt AE that has suicide attempt or gesture without intent to die which may not require hospitalization
a suicide attempt AE that has suicide attempt with intent to die which requires hospitalization
an aphonia AE that has voicelessness; unable to speak

label.value: Grade 1 depressed level of consciousness AE

definition.value: a depressed level of consciousness AE that has decreased level of alertness

label.value: Grade 2 depressed level of consciousness AE

definition.value: a depressed level of consciousness AE that has Sedation; slow response to stimuli; limiting instrumental ADL

label.value: Grade 3 depressed level of consciousness AE

definition.value: a depressed level of consciousness AE that is difficult to arouse
a dysgenusia AE that has altered taste but no change in diet
a dysgenusia AE that has altered taste with change in diet (e.g., oral supplements); noxious or unpleasant taste; loss of taste

a leukoencephalopathy AE that has asymptomatic; small focal T2/FLAIR hyperintensities; involving periventricular white matter or <1/3 of susceptible areas of cerebrum +/- mild increase in subarachnoid space (SAS) and/or mild ventriculomegaly

a leukoencephalopathy AE that has moderate symptoms; focal T2/FLAIR hyperintensities, involving periventricular white matter extending into centrum semiovale or involving 1/3 to 2/3 of susceptible areas of cerebrum +/- moderate increase in SAS and/or moderate ventriculomegaly

a leukoencephalopathy AE that has severe symptoms; extensive T2/FLAIR hyperintensities, involving periventricular white matter involving 2/3 or more of susceptible areas of cerebrum +/- moderate to severe increase in SAS and/or moderate to severe ventriculomegaly

a leukoencephalopathy AE that has life-threatening consequences; extensive T2/FLAIR hyperintensities, involving periventricular white matter involving most of susceptible areas of cerebrum +/- moderate to severe increase in SAS and/or moderate to severe ventriculomegaly
a myelitis AE that has asymptomatic; mild signs (e.g., Babinski's reflex or Lhermitte's sign)
a myelitis AE that has moderate weakness or sensory loss; limiting instrumental ADL
a myelitis AE that has severe weakness or sensory loss; limiting self care ADL
a presyncope AE that has present (e.g., near fainting)
a seizure AE that has brief partial seizure; no loss of consciousness
a seizure AE that has brief generalized seizure
a seizure AE that has multiple seizures despite medical intervention
a seizure AE that has life-threatening; prolonged repetitive seizures
a somnolence AE that has mild but more than usual drowsiness or sleepiness
a somnolence AE that has moderate sedation; limiting instrumental ADL
a somnolence AE that has obtundation or stupor
a syncope AE that has fainting; orthostatic collapse
an arthritis AE that has mild pain with inflammation, erythema, or joint swelling
